1. GRANT OF LICENCE
   Subject to a valid Rapidly licence and the terms of any separate
   commercial agreement with Rapidly Labs AS, you are granted a
   non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable licence to:
     (a) embed the SDK binaries within your own end-user applications,
         products, or services;
     (b) load the audio model files distributed with the SDK or supplied
         to you by Rapidly Labs AS, but only the model identifiers and
         latency variants encoded in your Rapidly licence ("model
         entitlements").

2. LICENCE TYPES

   The SDK enforces licence terms locally. Each Rapidly licence carries
   a cryptographically signed payload encoding the issuing account, a
   unique key identifier, expiration, and model entitlements (per-
   model_id, per-latency_ms).

   2.1 Licence Keys
       A Rapidly licence key is a perpetual offline credential of the
       form `lk_<base64url-payload>.<base64url-signature>`. The SDK
       verifies the key's Ed25519 signature against an embedded public
       key, checks expiration, and enforces model entitlements at model-
       load time without requiring any network access.

   (Future Rapidly licence types will be added as additional subsections
   under §2.)

